RACE.RACE_TEXT: OAKLAWN PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Claiming Purse 26000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Arkansas Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEVY settled off the pace while three wide through the first turn, continued in the three path when asked midway on the second bend, firm handling, late surge to be up in the final strides. FIVE O FOX cleared toward the inside early in the first turn after breaking alertly, dueled in the run into the far turn, disposed of that rival to be well clear into the lane, caved late to be caught in the waning strides. RIANTE SKY off a step slow, remained void of speed for five furlongs, advanced three to four wide turning for home, continued a mild rally while not a threat to the top two. LOBO IRISH in the main group while four wide through the first turn, continued outside, four wide again through most of the second bend, lacked a closing response to finish up evenly. OTHER TIMES well back, trailed second turn, picked off a couple of tiring horses while not a threat. DABOOGEYMAN rank while between horses first turn, advanced to duel up the backstretch, began to give way far turn, continued to tire through the stretch. BLAME IT pulled early along the inside when forwardly placed, stopped after a half, far back.

ENTRY.OWNER: McCord Carson and Southern Springs Stables (Ron Moquett)
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled off pace 3w, asked 2nd, 3w,late surge, just up

ENTRY.COMMENT: cleared toward rail, pace, shook well clear, caved late

ENTRY.COMMENT: pulled inside, forward, stopped after half

ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow, void of speed, 3-4w 1/4, mild rally,no match top 2

ENTRY.COMMENT: rank 1st turn, btwn, dueled, gave way

IMMORAL in the second flight early off the inside, four wide into the far turn when beginning to weaken, continued to falter in the drive. FETCHS BRAHM trailed throughout in showing little.

JOE BILL settled off the pace just off the inside, continued in the two path turn, improved position while not a serious threat. MATTFOLEYVANMAN broke alertly, showed the way clear up the backstretch and into the turn, allowed the winner the rail midway on the bend, began to weaken when headed by the two challengers in the turn. ANDREW'S VISION balked at loading, dwelt at the start, fell further and further back, distanced after losing contact with the field.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COURAGEOUS CAPPEN forwardly placed along the inside, patiently handled when covered up in traffic with three furlongs to run, asked along when having room midway on the bend while continuing inside, rail bid nearing the furlong ground, put a head in front late and proved game with holding off the runner up. COROMANDEL forwardly placed up the backstretch while three wide, vied into the stretch, dueled late outside the winner, outkicked by that one late while holding sway for the place. HONEYCAMP broke alertly, got clear before a furlongs, continued to hold a slight advantage through the turn and upper stretch, gave ground stubbornly to the top two while between them inside the furlong marker. DRIVING dropped inside when lacking speed, continued to save ground through the turn, improved position to the wire while not a serious threat to the top three. ELMO'S SECRET void of speed, remained back through, asked in the two path entering the stretch, mild rally to improve position. MY MOONLIGHT LADY in the second fight while off the inside, came three wide for the drive, went evenly to the wire in lacking a kick. BOOTLEGGING GIRL in the second group while racing outside, four wide for the drive, failed to muster a rally. BROOKE'S ALL IN racked in mid pack while along the inside, had little for the drive. RELENTLESS ROCKET hesitated at the break, raced well back early, four wide through the turn, made little impact through the stretch. EBBI BLU was finished early, far back.

Non-winners Of A Race Since January 9, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 9, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. (Horses Which Have Never Won A Race At A Mile Or Over A llowed 3 lbs.) Claiming Price $100,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MENDELSSOHNS MARCH behind the first flight along the inside first turn, continued behind the pace into the far bend, traffic while continuing along the rail, briefly waited approaching the furlong ground, got through, bid, edged clear. EL TOMATE off a step slow, void of speed in trailing, advanced three down to the two path second turn, traffic, bothered a furlong out, finished willingly after recovering to annex the place. SILVER HEIST off a step slow, raced between rivals in mid pack, came three wide for the drive, came out to lightly bump FUNNY UNCLE, lugged in past the furlong marker to tighten up inner rivals, was straightened, finished clear of the others while outkicked for the place. B MINOR four wide and forwardly placed into the first turn, continued within striking distance while toward the inside second turn, was idling when forced to steady when in tight between horses with a furlong to run, continued evenly to the finish. JUDO prompted the leader while racing off the inside for five furlongs, crept a bit closer in the second turn, was beginning to tire when he drifted in past the furlong marker, bumped in tight soon after and continued to weaken to the wire. HEROIC MOVE too, command after the start, set a moderate pace toward, clear of trouble with a furlong to run, caved late to lose several positions. LINE TO GAIN lacked speed while racing outside, roused when four wide out of the final turn, lacked a closing kick. FUNNY UNCLE within striking distance while four wide first turn, continued outside, was floated out four wide by SILVER HEIST turning for home, lightly bumped with that one, had nothing left. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY REGARDING THE STRETCH RUN, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
